```dockerfile
FROM rust:1.78 AS chef
WORKDIR /app
RUN cargo install cargo-chef
COPY Cargo.toml Cargo.lock ./
RUN cargo chef prepare --recipe-path recipe.json

FROM rust:1.78 AS rust-builder
WORKDIR /app
COPY --from=chef /app/recipe.json recipe.json
RUN cargo install cargo-chef
RUN cargo chef cook --release --recipe-path recipe.json
COPY server/ ./server/
COPY Cargo.toml Cargo.lock ./
RUN cargo build --release --manifest-path server/Cargo.toml

FROM python:3.11-bookworm AS python-builder
WORKDIR /app
RUN python -m venv /opt/venv
ENV PATH="/opt/venv/bin:$PATH"
RUN pip install --upgrade pip setuptools wheel
RUN pip install --no-cache-dir \
    torch==2.1.2 \
    transformers==4.36.2 \
    tokenizers==0.14.1 \
    safetensors==0.4.1
RUN pip install --no-cache-dir pyo3==0.20.0

FROM debian:bookworm-slim AS runtime
WORKDIR /app

# Install runtime dependencies
RUN apt-get update && apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends \
    ca-certificates \
    libssl3 \
    curl \
    && rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*

# Create non-root user
RUN useradd -m -u 1000 inference

# Copy Python virtualenv
COPY --from=python-builder /opt/venv /opt/venv

# Copy Rust binary
COPY --from=rust-builder /app/server/target/release/inference-server /usr/local/bin/

# Set permissions
RUN chown -R inference:inference /app

USER inference

ENV PATH="/opt/venv/bin:$PATH"
ENV PYTHONUNBUFFERED=1

EXPOSE 8080

HEALTHCHECK --interval=30s --timeout=10s --start-period=5s --retries=3 \
    CMD curl -f http://localhost:8080/health || exit 1

LABEL maintainer="inference-team"
LABEL description="Production Rust + Python ML Inference Server"
LABEL version="1.0"

CMD ["/usr/local/bin/inference-server", "--port", "8080"]
